# Fluff Date: 2026-02-19 16:29:24
overview:<p>The Storm Giant is a Golden Century-era Clan Steel Viper assault BattleMech, first produced around 2862 at the Novy Minsky Armaments Plant on New Kent. Commissioned by Khan Sanra Mercer to defend the Steel Vipers' homeworld, the 100-ton design was purpose-built to exploit New Kent's extreme equatorial heat, pairing high heat dissipation with low-heat weapons to overwhelm opponents already struggling with the planet's punishing environment. The Storm Giant served as a cornerstone of the Steel Viper touman for centuries, filling roles from flanker and harasser in lighter stars to frontline aggressor in heavy assault formations. Its combination of speed, firepower, and durability made it a versatile anchor in both defensive and offensive operations. Though the design's popularity eventually waned as other Clans adapted to Steel Viper tactics, the Storm Giant saw continuous service well into the Clan Invasion era before being rebuilt as the Scylla beginning in 3062.</p>

capabilities:<p>New Kent's blistering heat drove the Storm Giant's design philosophy. The planet's low elevation valleys routinely exceed equatorial averages, making thermal management critical for any 'Mech operating there. Steel Viper engineers responded by pairing a New Kent Type 50 XL 400 engine with seventeen double heat sinks and a weapons suite dominated by low-heat systems. Twin Type XX "Great Bow" LRM-20 launchers provide devastating long-range firepower, each fed by two tons of ammunition, while a Devastator Ultra 20 autocannon and paired Pattern J6 Streak SRM-6 launchers deliver overwhelming close-range damage. The Streak launchers are particularly efficient, wasting no ammunition on missed shots, though the Ultra autocannon can deplete its three-ton supply quickly if used aggressively.</p><p>Built on a Viper NK12 Endo Steel frame, the Storm Giant carries eighteen and a half tons of Compound V6 standard armor with CASE protecting all ammunition bins. Despite its 100-ton mass, the XL engine pushes it to a respectable 64 kilometers per hour, unusual speed for an assault 'Mech. This mobility allows it to function as a flanker or harasser rather than a static fire platform, though the lack of jump jets limits its tactical flexibility on broken terrain.</p>

deployment:<p>The Storm Giant 2 replaced the original's paired Pattern J6 Streak SRM-6 launchers with two extended-range large lasers and an ER medium laser, trading close-range missile punch for sustained long-range energy firepower. An additional double heat sink helps manage the increased thermal load, while a switch from standard Compound V6 armor to ferro-fibrous plating maintains protection at reduced weight. This variant was designed for combat off-world and in the cooler areas of New Kent where the base model's heat advantages were less relevant. Ultimately more popular with Steel Viper warriors, the Storm Giant 2 became the dominant variant of the design before its reconstruction into the Scylla.</p>

history:<p>The Storm Giant was born of necessity during the Golden Century, when Khan Sanra Mercer sought to isolate the Steel Vipers from the corrupting influence of rival Clans. Anticipating that the Grand Council would fear the Steel Vipers were following the path of the Annihilated Wolverines, Mercer ordered production of a new assault 'Mech optimized for combat on New Kent, the Vipers' homeworld. The resulting design exploited New Kent's extreme heat to give Steel Viper warriors a decisive advantage against invading forces.</p><p>The Storm Giant quickly proved its worth in the Vipers' frequent Trials and territorial disputes. In one notable engagement, a pair of Storm Giants formed part of a Star defending against a Clan Ghost Bear Trial of Possession for new OmniMech technology. The clash was unusual, as Ghost Bears and Steel Vipers did not often face each other in Trials. The Storm Giants dominated the engagement, shrugging off repeated Gauss slugs from Ghost Bear Minsks while closing to devastating autocannon range, ultimately overwhelming the Ghost Bear attackers including the enemy commander's Annihilator C.</p><p>Featured in every heavy and assault formation within the Steel Viper touman, the Storm Giant served variously as a flanker, harasser, and line breaker depending on the composition of its Star. In defensive assault stars it chased down the slowest enemy 'Mechs, while in lighter formations it acted as an immovable anchor of firepower. Only the fastest opponents could consistently avoid its weapons, and those unfortunate enough to be caught rarely survived long.</p><p>As the Clan Invasion era brought the proliferation of OmniMech technology, other Clans grew better able to counter the Steel Vipers' heat-exploitation tactics, and the Storm Giant's dominance began to fade. The Storm Giant 2, better configured for varied environments and longer-range combat, became the preferred variant. By the early 3060s, the aftermath of the Clan Invasion saw the Storm Giant reborn as the Scylla, trading the original's short-range autocannon for a longer-ranged weapon and adding jump jets for dramatically improved maneuverability.</p>

